            "answer_text": "In most cases, a burnt laptop adapter means a burnt capacitor. That\u2019s where the burning smell comes from. At times, the wires might get burnt as well. Unless you have prior experience in electrical repair and soldering, it\u2019s not recommended to open up an adapter. you might cause further damage to the wiring. Any electronics shop can easily fix it for you at nominal costs. ",
